:
exit

git checkout -b feature/breaking-change
.
.
.
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull
git checkout -b hotfix/some-prod-fix
.
.
.
git checkout feature/breaking-change
git pull origin main   # or rebase if you prefer cleaner history


You can't have outstanding changes in between these transitions. So even if there is a breaking change, thinking in terms of quick updates and commits so that there are no untracked files which will poison the context switch.